          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">Arab leaders pose during the emergency Arab summit at Egypt's New Administrative Capital. Credits: Egyptian Presidency Media Office via AP</p>
        </mj-text> 

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Arab leaders have gathered for a summit in Cairo to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-05-03-2025-h1-1-discuss-the-future-of-gaza?source=website" target="_blank">discuss the future of Gaza</a> and create an alternative to Trump’s Gaza plan. Egyptian President Abdel Fattah al-Sisi is heading the summit. Al-Sisi announced a plan prepared by Cairo for rebuilding Gaza without displacing its residents. The proposed plan for Gaza excludes Hamas from governance and outlines the creation of a temporary Palestinian committee to manage the enclave.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;filter:blur(5px);">The committee would consist of independent professionals and technocrats under the Palestinian Authority's (PA) guidance. Their role would be to oversee relief efforts, address Gaza’s challenges, and help prepare the territory for the PA's return. This plan ensures stability in Gaza while emphasizing a political solution that preserves the two-state approach.
       </p>
        </mj-text>
